President Obama made several phone calls to express his gratitude and congratulations for the passage of the Affordable Health Care for America Act. He called Nancy Pelosi, the Speaker of the House, and other Democratic leaders to thank them for their hard work. He also contacted Barry Rand, CEO of AARP, Rebecca Patton, President of the American Nurses Association, and Rebecca Patchin, President of the Board of Trustees of the American Medical Association, to thank them for their support, which was crucial for the approval of the legislation.